# C++ SOP

- Prefer modern C++ (C++17/20) when the project allows; RAII for ownership; no raw `new`/`delete` in new code.
- Const-correctness, explicit ownership (`unique_ptr` / `shared_ptr`); forward-declare when possible.
- Avoid macros where templates, `constexpr`, or enums suffice; minimize includes in headers.
- Match build system (CMake, Bazel, Makefile); do not hand-edit generated build files.
- Exceptions or error codes — follow project style; never mix silently.
- Move semantics for heavy types; rule of zero/five for resource-owning classes.
- Concurrency: prefer standard library primitives; document shared state lifetimes.
- Tests: `ctest`, `ninja test`, `make test`; ASan/UBSan builds when the repo supports them.
- No undefined behavior shortcuts; validate bounds and lifetimes at API boundaries.
